      • atTile

        Checks if player is at that specific tile within your set worldmap
        Parameters:
        tileToCheck - The tile to be checked for presence within the region defined in the map file.
        Returns:

      • isTileWithinArea

        boolean isTileWithinArea​(Tile tileToCheck,
                         Area areaToCheckWithin)
        Checks if a given tile is within a specified area.

        This method determines whether the provided tile (represented by tileToCheck) is located within the bounds of the area defined by areaToCheckWithin.

        Parameters:
        tileToCheck - The tile whose presence within the area is being checked.
        areaToCheckWithin - The area within which the tile's presence is checked.
        Returns:
        true if tileToCheck is within the bounds of areaToCheckWithin, false otherwise.

      • isTileWithinRegionbox

        boolean isTileWithinRegionbox​(Tile tileToCheck,
                              RegionBox regionToCheckWithin)
        Checks if a given tile is within a specified area.

        This method determines whether the provided tile (represented by tileToCheck) is located within the bounds of the RegionBox defined by regionToCheckWithin.

        Parameters:
        tileToCheck - The tile whose presence within the area is being checked.
        regionToCheckWithin - The RegionBox within which the tile's presence is checked.
        Returns:
        true if tileToCheck is within the bounds of areaToCheckWithin, false otherwise.

      • tileEquals

        boolean tileEquals​(Tile originTile,
                   Tile tileToCheck)
        Compares two tiles for equality.

        This method checks if the specified originTile and tileToCheck represent the same tile.

        Parameters:
        originTile - The first tile to be compared.
        tileToCheck - The second tile to be compared with the first tile.
        Returns:
        true if both tiles are considered equal, false otherwise.
